Dialogue: 0,00:01:54.000,00:01:55.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's called the shallow water equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:55.000,00:01:58.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's called the shallow water equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:58.000,00:02:04.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,Shallow water equation is the equation that models the movement of water, of any fluid,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:04.000,00:02:10.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,under the influence of gravity, a shallow layer of water.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:10.000,00:02:18.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,It actually describes, for example, the waves on a beach pretty well before it breaks.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:18.000,00:02:19.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,00:02:19.000,00:02:23.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you can do a lot of interesting experiments with it.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:23.000,00:02:25.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the reason actually...
Dialogue: 0,00:02:25.000,00:02:29.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you look at the movement of waves over a beach,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:29.000,00:02:33.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the reason the wave breaks is...
Dialogue: 0,00:02:33.000,00:02:40.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this shallow water equation, it's going to appear as a shock wave in the shallow water equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:40.000,00:02:45.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,You're going to create a discontinuity in the height of the water,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:45.000,00:02:51.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,which in real case, it'll just fall down and break as a wave.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:51.000,00:02:52.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in the shallow water equation, it's going to be like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:52.000,00:02:58.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in the shallow water equation, the two quantities we are modeling
Dialogue: 0,00:02:58.000,00:03:01.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,are first of all the height of the water.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:01.000,00:03:07.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you have, let's say, a water column like that.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:07.000,00:03:12.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the height of the water, and also the velocity of the water.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:12.000,00:03:18.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right, how fast the water is moving, either towards the left or towards the right.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:18.000,00:03:20.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And in reality,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:20.000,00:03:29.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,the reason that h is a conservative quantity is because we are modeling water as incompressible.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:29.000,00:03:37.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So h integrated over x is what?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:37.000,00:03:41.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if you integrate h over x,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:41.000,00:03:45.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's the volume, it's how much water you have.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:45.000,00:03:49.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And velocity doesn't really integrate to be a conservative quantity.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:49.000,00:03:56.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So instead, we use u times h as a conservative variable.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:56.000,00:04:06.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you multiply u over h and integrate over dx, what do you get?
